<paragraph id="8BD28D2EFFCD3D4D81A0105EFE8FFE9F" blockId="8.[151,331,267,293]" box="[151,331,267,293]" pageId="8" pageNumber="11">
<heading id="D09A3A42FFCD3D4D81A0105EFE8FFE9F" bold="true" box="[151,331,267,293]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="8" pageNumber="11" reason="1">
<taxonomicName id="4C6DF6ADFFCD3D4D81A0105EFE8FFE9F" box="[151,331,267,293]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Tripterygiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="11" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">
<emphasis id="B919513CFFCD3D4D81A0105EFE8FFE9F" bold="true" box="[151,331,267,293]" pageId="8" pageNumber="11">Tripterygiidae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD28D2EFFCD3D4D81F1100CFC91FDE1" blockId="8.[151,1436,345,912]" pageId="8" pageNumber="11">
<number id="3DA59F09FFCD3D4D81F1100CFF21FEC9" box="[198,229,345,371]" pageId="8" pageNumber="11" value="20.0">20</number>
) 
<taxonomicName id="4C6DF6ADFFCD3D4D81C0100CFE4DFEC8" box="[247,393,345,370]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Tripterygiidae" genus="Tripterygion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="11" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919513CFFCD3D4D81C0100CFE4DFEC8" box="[247,393,345,370]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="11">Tripterygion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFCF0DFFFCD3D4D80AB100CFD91FEC9" author="Zander" box="[412,597,345,371]" pageId="8" pageNumber="14" refString="Zander, C. D. (1986 b) Tripterygiidae. In: Whitehead, P. J. P., Bauchot, M. L., Hureau, J. C., Nielsen, J. &amp; Tortonese, E. (Eds.), Fishes of the North-eastern Atlantic and Mediterranean (Volume 3). UNESCO, Paris, pp. 1118 - 1121." type="journal article" year="1986" yearSuffix="b">
Zander (
<number id="3DA59F09FFCD3D4D8336100CFDFAFEC9" box="[513,574,345,371]" pageId="8" pageNumber="11" value="1986.0">1986</number>
b)
</bibRefCitation>
recognized two subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6DF6ADFFCD3D4D82FD100CFAADFEC9" authority="Guichenot" authorityName="Guichenot" box="[970,1385,345,371]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Tripterygiidae" genus="Tripterygion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="11" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="melanurus">
<emphasis id="B919513CFFCD3D4D82FD100CFB27FEC8" box="[970,1251,345,370]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="11">Tripterygion melanurus</emphasis>
Guichenot
</taxonomicName>
, the nominate from the eastern and southern Mediterranean including the Balearics (
<typeStatus id="54D6338CFFCD3D4D850B10D5FBB4FE20" box="[1084,1136,384,410]" pageId="8" pageNumber="11">type</typeStatus>
locality: 
<collectingCountry id="F37ACDBEFFCD3D4D85D210D5FA86FE20" box="[1253,1346,384,410]" name="Algeria" pageId="8" pageNumber="11">Algeria</collectingCountry>
), and 
<emphasis id="B919513CFFCD3D4D84B110D5FEC5FE7A" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="11">
T. m. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6DF6ADFFCD3D4D818C10F2FEC5FE7A" authority="Kolombatovic" authorityName="Kolombatovic" box="[187,257,423,448]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Tripterygiidae" genus="Tripterygion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="11" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="minor">minor</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
Kolombatovic from the northern Mediterranean (
<typeStatus id="54D6338CFFCD3D4D827F10F3FCB8FE7A" box="[840,892,422,448]" pageId="8" pageNumber="11">type</typeStatus>
locality: Split, Dalmatia) based on coloration (caudal peduncle spot present in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6DF6ADFFCD3D4D83141098FD64FE5C" box="[547,672,461,486]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Tripterygiidae" genus="Tripterygion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="11" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="melanurus">
<emphasis id="B919513CFFCD3D4D83141098FD64FE5C" box="[547,672,461,486]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="11">melanurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, absent in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6DF6ADFFCD3D4D82131098FCAFFE5C" box="[804,875,461,486]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Tripterygiidae" genus="Tripterygion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="11" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis id="B919513CFFCD3D4D82131098FCAFFE5C" box="[804,875,461,486]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="11">minor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFCF0DFFFCD3D4D82B21098FB85FE5D" author="Zander" box="[901,1089,461,487]" pageId="8" pageNumber="14" refString="Zander, C. D. (1986 b) Tripterygiidae. In: Whitehead, P. J. P., Bauchot, M. L., Hureau, J. C., Nielsen, J. &amp; Tortonese, E. (Eds.), Fishes of the North-eastern Atlantic and Mediterranean (Volume 3). UNESCO, Paris, pp. 1118 - 1121." type="journal article" year="1986" yearSuffix="b">
Zander (
<number id="3DA59F09FFCD3D4D82DD1098FBECFE5D" box="[1002,1064,461,487]" pageId="8" pageNumber="11" value="1986.0">1986</number>
b)
</bibRefCitation>
also noted the occurrence of hybrid populations and a recent genetic study (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFCF0DFFFCD3D4D83F510A1FBF7FDB4" author="Carreras-Carbonell" box="[706,1075,500,526]" pageId="8" pageNumber="12" refString="Carreras-Carbonell, J., Macpherson, E. &amp; Pascual, M. (2005) Rapid radiation and cryptic speciation in Mediterranean triplefin blennies (Pisces: Tripterygiidae) combining multiple genes. Molecular Phylogenetics &amp; Evolution, 37, 751 - 761." type="journal article" year="2005">
Carreras-Carbonell et al., 
<number id="3DA59F09FFCD3D4D82C010A1FBF7FDB4" box="[1015,1075,500,526]" pageId="8" pageNumber="11" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) found no differences in these two and did not recommend retaining their nomenclatural distinction. Thus, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6DF6ADFFCD3D4D851B134FFB54FD89" box="[1068,1168,538,563]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Tripterygiidae" genus="Tripterygion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="11" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis id="B919513CFFCD3D4D851B134FFB54FD89" box="[1068,1168,538,563]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="11">T. minor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is considered a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6DF6ADFFCD3D4D801E1314FE06FDE0" box="[297,450,577,602]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Tripterygiidae" genus="Tripterygion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="11" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="melanurus">
<emphasis id="B919513CFFCD3D4D801E1314FE06FDE0" box="[297,450,577,602]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="11">T. melanurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in accordance with 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFCF0DFFFCD3D4D83991314FC96FDE1" author="Fricke" box="[686,850,577,603]" pageId="8" pageNumber="12" refString="Fricke, R. (1997) Tripterygiid fishes of the western and central Pacific, with descriptions of 15 new species, including an annotated checklist of world Tripterygiidae (Teleostei). Tripterygiid Fishes of the Western Central Pacific, Koeltz Scientific Books, Koenigstein, Germany, 607 pp." type="book" year="1997">
Fricke (
<number id="3DA59F09FFCD3D4D823E1314FC8DFDE1" box="[777,841,577,603]" pageId="8" pageNumber="11" value="1997.0">1997</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C377DEA5FFCD3D4D81F1133DFF27FC2A" pageId="8" pageNumber="11" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD28D2EFFCD3D4D81F1133DFF27FC2A" blockId="8.[151,1436,345,912]" pageId="8" pageNumber="11">
<number id="3DA59F09FFCD3D4D81F1133DFF20FD38" box="[198,228,616,642]" pageId="8" pageNumber="11" value="21.0">21</number>
) 
<taxonomicName id="4C6DF6ADFFCD3D4D81CE133DFE4FFD3B" box="[249,395,616,641]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Tripterygiidae" genus="Tripterygion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="11" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919513CFFCD3D4D81CE133DFE4FFD3B" box="[249,395,616,641]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="11">Tripterygion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFCF0DFFFCD3D4D80A8133DFD9FFD38" author="Zander" box="[415,603,616,642]" pageId="8" pageNumber="14" refString="Zander, C. D. (1986 b) Tripterygiidae. In: Whitehead, P. J. P., Bauchot, M. L., Hureau, J. C., Nielsen, J. &amp; Tortonese, E. (Eds.), Fishes of the North-eastern Atlantic and Mediterranean (Volume 3). UNESCO, Paris, pp. 1118 - 1121." type="journal article" year="1986" yearSuffix="b">
Zander (
<number id="3DA59F09FFCD3D4D8330133DFD80FD38" box="[519,580,616,642]" pageId="8" pageNumber="11" value="1986.0">1986</number>
b)
</bibRefCitation>
recognized 
<taxonomicName id="4C6DF6ADFFCD3D4D83C3133DFAE3FD38" authority="Cadenat &amp; Blache" authorityName="Cadenat &amp; Blache" box="[756,1319,616,642]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Tripterygiidae" genus="Tripterygion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="11" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="delaisi" subSpecies="delaisi">
<emphasis id="B919513CFFCD3D4D83C3133DFBFEFD3B" box="[756,1082,616,641]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="11">Tripterygion delaisi delaisi</emphasis>
Cadenat &amp; Blache
</taxonomicName>
from the eastern Atlantic excluding the Mediterranean Sea (
<typeStatus id="54D6338CFFCD3D4D823E13DBFC84FD12" box="[777,832,654,680]" pageId="8" pageNumber="11">type</typeStatus>
locality: 
<collectingCountry id="F37ACDBEFFCD3D4D828813DBFBC9FD12" box="[959,1037,654,680]" name="Senegal" pageId="8" pageNumber="11">Gorée</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F37ACDBEFFCD3D4D852D13DBFB44FD12" box="[1050,1152,654,680]" name="Senegal" pageId="8" pageNumber="11">Senegal</collectingCountry>
), and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6DF6ADFFCD3D4D85FD13DAFEABFD75" authority="Zander &amp; Heymer" authorityName="Zander &amp; Heymer" class="Actinopterygii" family="Tripterygiidae" genus="Tripterygion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="11" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="delaisi" subSpecies="xanthosoma">
<emphasis id="B919513CFFCD3D4D85FD13DAFA58FD12" box="[1226,1436,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="11">T. d. xanthosoma</emphasis>
Zander &amp; Heymer
</taxonomicName>
from the Mediterranean (
<typeStatus id="54D6338CFFCD3D4D83A913E0FD16FD75" box="[670,722,693,719]" pageId="8" pageNumber="11">type</typeStatus>
locality: Banyuls-sur-Mer, 
<collectingCountry id="F37ACDBEFFCD3D4D851713E0FBB1FD75" box="[1056,1141,693,719]" name="France" pageId="8" pageNumber="11">France</collectingCountry>
). These forms reportedly differ in courtship behavior and ecology. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFCF0DFFFCD3D4D83B01389FCDBFD4C" author="Wirtz" box="[647,799,732,758]" pageId="8" pageNumber="14" refString="Wirtz, P. (1990) Tripterygiidae. In: Quero, J. - C., Hureau, J. C., Karrer, C., Post, A. Saldanha, L. (Eds.), Check-list of the fishes of the eastern tropical Atlantic. Unesco, Paris, pp. 916 - 917." type="book chapter" year="1990">
Wirtz (
<number id="3DA59F09FFCD3D4D83EE1389FCD2FD4C" box="[729,790,732,758]" pageId="8" pageNumber="11" value="1990.0">1990</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFCF0DFFFCD3D4D826D1389FC38FD4C" author="Fricke" box="[858,1020,732,758]" pageId="8" pageNumber="12" refString="Fricke, R. (1997) Tripterygiid fishes of the western and central Pacific, with descriptions of 15 new species, including an annotated checklist of world Tripterygiidae (Teleostei). Tripterygiid Fishes of the Western Central Pacific, Koeltz Scientific Books, Koenigstein, Germany, 607 pp." type="book" year="1997">
Fricke (
<number id="3DA59F09FFCD3D4D82821389FC36FD4C" box="[949,1010,732,758]" pageId="8" pageNumber="11" value="1997.0">1997</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
considered the latter a synonym of the former. Recent genetic studies (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFCF0DFFFCD3D4D83061257FC5BFCA6" author="Carreras-Carbonell" box="[561,927,770,796]" pageId="8" pageNumber="12" refString="Carreras-Carbonell, J., Macpherson, E. &amp; Pascual, M. (2005) Rapid radiation and cryptic speciation in Mediterranean triplefin blennies (Pisces: Tripterygiidae) combining multiple genes. Molecular Phylogenetics &amp; Evolution, 37, 751 - 761." type="journal article" year="2005">
Carreras-Carbonell et al., 
<number id="3DA59F09FFCD3D4D82561257FC5BFCA6" box="[865,927,770,796]" pageId="8" pageNumber="11" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFCF0DFFFCD3D4D829D1257FB7FFCA6" author="Domingues" box="[938,1211,770,796]" pageId="8" pageNumber="12" refString="Domingues, V. S., Almada, V. C., Santos, R. S., Brito, A. &amp; Bernardi, G. (2007) Phylogeography and evolution of the triplefin Tripterygion delaise (Pisces, Blennioidei). Marine Biology, 150, 509 - 519." type="journal article" year="2007">
Domingues et al., 
<number id="3DA59F09FFCD3D4D85481257FB7FFCA6" box="[1151,1211,770,796]" pageId="8" pageNumber="11" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) found evidence of two lineages, however, it is not clear that the genetic differences parallel the phenotypic (and nomenclatural) differences. Consequently, resolution of the status of these forms awaits further study (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFCF0DFFFCD3D4D85F61205FF13FC2A" author="Domingues" pageId="8" pageNumber="12" refString="Domingues, V. S., Almada, V. C., Santos, R. S., Brito, A. &amp; Bernardi, G. (2007) Phylogeography and evolution of the triplefin Tripterygion delaise (Pisces, Blennioidei). Marine Biology, 150, 509 - 519." type="journal article" year="2007">
Domingues et al., 
<number id="3DA59F09FFCD3D4D81A01223FF13FC2A" box="[151,215,886,912]" pageId="8" pageNumber="11" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
